</head>

<body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=WordSection1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
line-height:normal;mso-outline-level:2'><a name=Adams><b><span
style='font-size:18.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:blue'>Twain:
Two Adams </span></b></a><span class=SpellE><span style='mso-bookmark:Adams'><b><span
style='font-size:18.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:blue'>vs</span></b></span></span><span
style='mso-bookmark:Adams'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman";color:blue'> Christ is neither Adam1 nor Adam2</span></b></span><span
style='mso-bookmark:Adams'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'><o:p></o:p></span></b></span></p>

<span style='mso-bookmark:Adams'></span>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal'><b><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";
color:black'>Two</span></b><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman";color:black'> </span></b><b><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black'>Adams</span></b><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";
color:black'> are <b>compared</b> in <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Bibles.htm">1Corinthians 15:45</a> as
first man Adam and last Adam; But in <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2Corinthians%2010:12&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="2Corinthians 10:12 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">2Corinthians
10:12</a> it's not wise (but foolish) to compare <span class=GramE>Adam1(</span>soul)
<span class=SpellE>vs</span> Adam2(spirit), and in if told compare spirit-u-all
<span class=SpellE>vs</span> spirit-u-all, which is to say compare Adam2(law) <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> Christ(grace). For <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Hebrews%204:12&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Hebrews 4:12 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Hebrews 4:12</a> has
two dividing <span class=SpellE>asunders</span> in order to get the heart of
the matter, as if first wrongly dividing the word of truth (law <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> law) and then rightly dividing the word of truth (laws <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> grace). <span class=GramE>things</span> divided against
itself nor wise to mix first and last = oxymoron. First/last Adams (<span
class=SpellE>thems</span>) are therein <b>contrasted</b> as soul/spirit, also
as natural/spiritual man, as if before/after; But notably also as first/second,
and clarified as earthly/heavenly &quot;<span class=SpellE>image&quot;s</span>,
leaving us with an <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Allegory.htm">allegoric
mystery</a> to sort out</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. For in <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Hebrews5.htm">Hebrews 4:12</a> the
dividing asunder of soul&lt;--&gt;spirit is only the first of two dividing <span
class=SpellE>asunders</span> required to get to the heart of the matter: If
your heart is not <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/RevelatorySermons1.htm">established</a>
&quot;with&quot; grace (<a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Hebrews14.htm">Hebrews
13:9</a>), then <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew%2012:30-37&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Matthew 12:30-37 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Matthew 12:30-37</a>'s
either or list clarifies it is &quot;against&quot;; And <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Romans%208:2&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Romans 8:2 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Romans 8:2</a>'s <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Romans8.html">Law1 <span class=SpellE>vs</span>
Law2</a> of <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1Corinthians%2015:45&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="1Corinthians 15:45 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">1Corinthians
15:45</a>'s Adam1 <span class=SpellE>vs</span> Adam2, which is also like <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Hebrews%2010:39&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Hebrews 10:39 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Hebrews 10:39</a>'s <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwainShew6.htm#Thems">Them1 <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> Them2</a>, are all notably divided &quot;against&quot;
itself, will notably <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Inexcusable.html">defile(condemn)
itself</a> with <span class=SpellE>it's</span> own mouth from the heart (<a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Mark%207:18-23&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Mark 7:18-23 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Mark 7:18-23</a>);
And thereby end up in a <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Hebrews12.htm">hall
of shame</a> rather than fame, for playing the <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/GodShew.htm#nomorechildren">childish</a> <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/RevelatorySermons15.htm">blame game</a>. <span
class=GramE>For whether it be playing <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TheirPartYourPart.htm">their part or your
part</a>, it's still <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Partiality.html">part-<span
class=SpellE>iality</span></a> and not <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/RevelatorySermons14.htm">perfect-ion</a>.</span>
For <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1Corinthians%2013:10&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="1Corinthians 13:10 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">1Corinthians
13:10</a> notes when perfect-ion is come, then part-<span class=SpellE>iality</span>
is done away. Furthermore, it's revealed in <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2Corinthians%2010:12&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="2Corinthians 10:12 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">2Corinthians
10:12</a> that comparing&nbsp; Them1 <span class=SpellE>vs</span> Them2 (Law1 <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> Law2, Adam1 <span class=SpellE>vs</span> Adam2) is not
wise: not a wise comparison, but a foolish comparison of <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwainShew2.htm#Childrens">children <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> children</a> and of <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwainShew6.htm#Servants">servants <span
class=SpellE>vs</span> servants</a> who are <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/RevelatorySermons10.htm">carnally</a>
divided against themselves, or &quot;oppose themselves&quot; as it says in <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2Timothy%202:25&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="2Timothy 2:25 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">2Timothy 2:25</a>;
Which is common and commonly called bi-polar <span class=SpellE>dis</span>-order,
or <a href="http://pub30.bravenet.com/forum/2526810710/show/1039287">PTSD</a>,
or <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/OneLiners.htm#BibleTranslators">preposterous
order</a> (teaching first and learning after) by <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/BibleTranslators.htm">Translators of the
Bible</a>. <br>
<br>
In 1st Adam (</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>&quot;<span
class=SpellE>natural&quot;man</span></span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>): &quot;all&quot; die;
evidently from a bad case of grace + law = life + death = a dead end. In last
Adam (</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>&quot;spiritual&quot;</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>man</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>)
is a <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/SAQs.htm">question</a>: <b>shall
all</b> be made alive? The correct answer is <span class=GramE>Yes</span>!
Reason: if not &quot;all&quot;, then none at all; <span class=GramE>For</span>
&quot;<b>there is no respect of persons with God</b>&quot;, nor with Son of
God. So you too can have partiality with impartial God is an oxymoronic </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(for <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/ShewBread7.htm#Bliss"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>morons</span></a>)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Law.htm">lie</a> witch many churches and
their leaders thereof preach as deceivers (ministers of <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/BiblicalDots.htm">Satan = Law</a>). Such
ministers (both religious &amp; political) are both good + evil, for <b>law is
both good + evil</b>; But <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Hebrews6.htm">Hebrews
5</a>'s conclusion exhorts us to use our senses to &quot;<span class=GramE><b>discern</b><span
style='font-size:10.0pt'>(</span></span></span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>avoid)</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> <b>both good + evil</b>&quot;.
If it looks a bit</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>(a little <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Law.htm"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>leaven</span></a> <span class=SpellE>leaveneth</span>
the whole)</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'> <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pFTjeaDlxDI">Fishy</a></span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(like the
license plates on many <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/RevelatorySermons10.htm"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>carnal</span></a></span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>cars)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
sounds like <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/MtSinai.htm"><span
class=SpellE>Horeb</span></a>-bull, smells <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/ShewBread9.htm#Expired"><span
class=SpellE>Pewy</span></a>, tastes Bitter-sweet (<a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/BiblicalDots.htm">Col 2:21</a>), and feels
like <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwainShew3.htm#Gods">hell</a> when
even &quot;tasted&quot;(<a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Hebrews7.htm">Heb
6</a>:4), or <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Allegory3.htm">worse</a>: <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Revelations9.htm">swallowed</a>, then it's<b>
law</b>: <b>both</b> <b>good + </b><a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/BiblicalDots.htm"><b>evil</b></a>, <span
class=SpellE>witch</span> <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/lawphoto.htm">ends
bad</a>.</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><br>
<br>
</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/SAQs.htm"><b>Seldom Asked Question</b></a>
<b>posed</b>: &quot;even so in Christ <b>shall all</b> be made alive&quot;<b>?</b>
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
text-align:center;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>Moral:&nbsp; God <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/ShewBread5.htm#willx2"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>will</span></a> be &quot;<a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/GodShew2.htm#Allness"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>all</span></a> in all&quot;,<span
class=GramE>&nbsp; not</span> some short fall like 2/3 = 0.666 to infinity of
nothing. <br>
Until <b>you</b> (all the <span class=SpellE>KofG</span> within <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/YeYou.htm"><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt'>you</span></a>) <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/GodsheworgExplanation.htm"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>get it</span></a>: <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Topics.htm"><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt'>understanding</span></a>, it seems that <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/GodShew4.htm#Probate"><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt'>all are <span class=SpellE>groundead</span></span></a>.</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
normal'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><br>
First Adam &quot;was&quot; </span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>a </span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>&quot;living <b>soul</b>&quot;, last Adam &quot;is&quot; </span><span
style='font-size:13.5pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a </span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>&quot;quickening
<b>spirit</b>&quot;; the allegorical difference being </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>mortal</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>/</span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>immortal
&amp; corruptible/incorruptible,</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> is also the difference between
grace + law / grace</span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>:</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'> <b>this</b> before <b>was</b>: &quot;earthy&quot;, <b>that</b>
after <b>is</b>: &quot;heavenly&quot;; similar to <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/YeYou.htm">ye/you</a> are before/after in <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Bibles.htm">1Peter 5:10</a></span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. </span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><br>
<br>
<a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/SAQs.htm"><span class=SpellE>Mirrorly</span>
speaking</a> (wherein center <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/biblicalemblems.htm">changed</a> to
right): as we have borne the image of <b>this</b> one man </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(1st Adam)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> we
shall <b>also</b> bear the &quot;express image&quot;</span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(<a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Heb%201&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Heb 1 (Bible Gateway: KJV)"><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt'>Heb 1</span></a>) </span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>of <b>that</b> one man </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(last Adam)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:
the change being from <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwainShew3.htm#Glorys">glory to glory</a> </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(law to
grace)</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>: <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2Cor%203&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="2Cor 3 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">2Cor 3</a>; from&nbsp; </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(blind)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
faith to </span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(<a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/CurrentEvents.htm"><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
11.0pt'>seeing</span></a>)</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> faith </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(is
&quot;better&quot;)</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>; and <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Sevens2.htm"><span
class=SpellE>mtn</span> to mtn</a>. The second </span><span style='font-size:
10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(of first/second)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
is: <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Usward.htm">the Lord</a> </span><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(of Lords)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
from heaven: &quot;<a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/ShewBread5.htm#IAMTHAT">that</a>&quot; of <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwainShew8.htm">this/that</a>. For <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/OneLiners.htm#JohnLewis">two contrary
things cannot coexist</a>, not in <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/through.htm">peace</a>, so he <span
class=SpellE>taketh</span> away the first to establish the second. He is our
&quot;<a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/PeaceLinks.htm">peace</a>&quot;
who hath <b>abolished</b> the <a
href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/TwoGods.htm">law(enmity)</a> from his
flesh (we are his flesh): <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians%202&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Ephesians 2 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Ephesians 2</a> (<a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Eph%205&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Eph 5 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Eph 5</a>)... concurs with <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Col%202&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Col 2 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Col 2</a>'s mention of
ordinances(law) being <b>blotted out</b>.<br>
<br>
See also the <b>one man</b> <span class=SpellE>vs</span> <b>one man</b> Twain
Shew in <a
href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Romans%205:12-21&amp;version=KJV"
target="_blank" title="Romans 5:12-21 (Bible Gateway: KJV)">Romans 5:12-21</a>.
By <b>this</b>: &quot;one man&quot; </span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>(Moses)</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
came <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/Law.htm"><b>the law</b></a>: <b>death</b>
upon all; <a href="http://localhost/xampp/godshew/GodShew3.htm#Second">Also</a>
by <b>that</b>: &quot;one man&quot; </span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
